release_text:
Horrordelic proudly presents Codex Gigas (Mexico) new EP release named: `The Night Of Horror`.

For dark and psychedelic tales all ready for your journey. Get ready for some real deal DarkPsy!

Tracks based on the world of Silent Hill. Stay tuned for a deep into your mental psyche and a beautiful yet dark atmosphere to both dance and listen to...

Tracks list and information:
01. La Bruja (The Witch 150 BPM) In the dark recesses of Silent Hill, there once existed an innocent girl, unjustly condemned by the ignorance and fear of men. The church, in its blind pursuit of what it did not understand, burned her alive within a shrine, believing her supernatural powers to be the work of evil.

The flames devoured her body as the villagers' curses echoed through the air, but her spirit survived, fueled by an insatiable thirst for vengeance. In the darkness of her suffering, the girl was reborn as an unstoppable force, ready to demand justice.

02. Fuego Purificador (Purifying Fire 150 BPM) The Order of Valtiel, fervent defenders of a twisted interpretation of faith, dedicated their lives to purifying souls with fire. In their crusade to restore supposed purity, they burned those they considered impure, convinced that this would prevent the apocalypse.

For years, her purifying fire consumed many innocents, leaving behind a trail of pain and ash. In Silent Hill, her actions echoed with despair and madness, perpetuating an endless cycle of torment.

03. Almas Perdidas (Lost Souls 150 BPM) A girl whose pain was so deep it burned within her, Alesa survived a brutal attempt to burn her alive. Hatred and despair took hold of her soul, transforming her into a dark, vengeful force.

Alesa let her hatred grow until her mere presence hurt the curious and unwary, allowing death to seep into their hearts. In the abyss of her suffering, she became a beacon of darkness, dragging those who dared come close to eternal damnation.

04. El Mundo de Alesa (Alesa's World 150 BPM) From the depths of her agony, Alesa created a world of darkness, filled with terrifying creatures that roamed Silent Hill. Her power transformed the town into a twisted reflection of her pain, a nightmare realm where fear and vengeance ruled.

Every corner and shadow of Silent Hill echoed with the screams of the damned, trapped in an endless cycle of horror and despair. Alesa, the architect of this hell, reveled in the terror she sowed, a living manifestation of the injustice she suffered.
credits:
Music + Art: Efect Mushroom
Mastering: Krono Audio
Release: Horrordelic

release_text:
Horrordelic proudly presents the new release from Efect Mushroom named “Historias de Terror”. 

Tracks and info: 

1. Sintonía Tenebrosa (155 BPM)
In the darkest depths, infernal voices intertwine with twisted beats. Like a pact sealed in blood, this tune awakens ancient entities. Are you ready to face the unknown?

(En las profundidades más oscuras, las voces infernales se entrelazan con los beats retorcidos. Como un pacto sellado en sangre, esta sintonía despierta entidades ancestrales. ¿Estás listo para enfrentarte a lo desconocido?)

2.- El Ritual Vudú (175 BPM)
In the dimness of a room, a witch stands before a sinister-looking doll. The air is charged with electricity, and the candles flicker like expectant eyes.

 This person holds a rusty knife and recites ancestral words. The doll trembles, its seams tear and its stuffing transforms.


 The witch's soul detaches itself, floating in the air, as the doll comes to life. Electronic drums mark the beat of this dark voodoo ritual, and the music becomes a channel for transmigration.

 (En la penumbra de una habitación, un brujo  se encuentra frente a un muñeco de aspecto siniestro. El aire está cargado de electricidad, y las velas parpadean como si fueran ojos expectantes. 

 Esta persona  sostiene un cuchillo oxidado y recita palabras ancestrales.

 El muñeco tiembla, sus costuras se desgarran y su relleno se transforma. El alma del brujo se desprende, flotando en el aire, mientras el muñeco cobra vida. Los tambores electrónicos marcan el compás de este oscuro ritual vudú, y la música se convierte en un canal para la transmigración.)

3.-Catacumbas Siniestras (180 BPM):
(Las Catacumbas de París se extienden como un laberinto de huesos. Entre las calaveras apiladas, los beats resuenan como profanaciones olvidadas. ¿Qué secretos yacen en estos pasillos subterráneos? La música te guiará hacia la verdad.)

4.- Seres de Ultratumba (175 BPM)
From the darkness, beings from beyond the grave emerge. They whisper in inaudible frequencies, like echoes of trapped souls. The beats drag you into a frenetic dance with the inexplicable.

Who are these specters? What message do they bring from beyond?

(Desde la penumbra, los seres ultratumba emergen. Susurran en frecuencias inaudibles, como ecos de almas atrapadas. Los beats te arrastran hacia una danza frenética con lo inexplicable.

¿Quiénes son estos espectros? ¿Qué mensaje traen desde el más allá?)

4 thrilling dark psychedelic tales are awaiting for you, get yourself ready and play these loud!
credits:
Music & Artwork by Efect Mushroom

Mastering Krono Audio

Release by Horrordelic 2024

release_text:
The Monsters of Darkness, ones of mankind's oldest enemies. They are fearsome monsters who lurk in the darkness of the moon. Nasty bunch. While there are good people among them, the majority of them are pure monsters. Where else do you think humans get their fear of the dark from, kiddo?

There are many definitions of what a creature of the night is. The main idea is that the Monsters of Darkness are a supernatural, mostly malevolent, creature that comes from the darkness of the moon or the world. Most are creatures born through unnatural means, some examples being cursed in the form of a monster or being turned into an undead creature. They are known as the opposites and enemies of the Fae and Angels, which also makes them the reluctant allies of the Demons.

They usually reside in the Nightland, a realm for them created by Death for those who seeks isolation from humanity either in distaste for them or in fear that they would be hunted down. However, unlike the Fae enemies, many of Monsters of darkness refuse to go the realm and so instead stay in the Human Realm as before.

Get ready for this Monster Gathering!

The Monsters will gather to celebrate another fearful full moon, filled with dark and malevolent forces, macabre symphonies and persuasive deadly percussions from beyond the spirit of death. Follow the arrows, venture out, join this magnificent Monster gathering all night! Be part of the Dark Circle, check out our Circle of Darkness.



But beware - you might never get out - once in!
credits:
Compiled by Psycholouis & Antikriz
Artwork by OMZIG & Antikriz
Mastering Krono Audio

release_text:
Horrordelic Proudly presents a new VA, celebrating our 10 Years in the scene. 

 The Realm of The Death: 
 The ancient Greeks believed in an underworld to which the souls of the dead journeyed. It was known by names such as Hades or Erebus which have become synonymous with the concept of ‘Hell’.

The Underworld was a structured place. The souls of the dead were sent to various realms based on how they were judged: blameless heroes to Elysium, the evil to Tartarus and those who were neither good nor bad to the Fields of Asphodel. To safely travel from the world of the living to that of Hades, the soul needed to cross the Styx (the River of Hate) on a boat steered by a grim ferryman known as Charon.

release_text:
Yata-Garasu - Shiki (15'th Anniversary & 4'th Solo Album) 

This Is a special 15 year celebration of his work in the scene, listen to his own words below: Nyanpasu. What can I say ... 15 years of the Yata-Garasu project.

 15 years of hard work.

 15 years of blood , sweat & lot's of tears. 

 ... 

 I would like to thank every single person that has been, is & will be in my life to come... You all know who you are & you all will be remembered forever & ever.

 Horrordelic records , My family (Kriz , Edel & Johnny).

 Anime... Without anime , I wouldn't be writing all this now.  Without anime , there would be no Yata-Garasu. Without anime there would be no Paul Hoeylaerts. 

But the biggest thank you goes out to YOU. For listening, experiencing, following & supporting my music. Even if you just tuned in to this project after 15 years ... THANK YOU!  

Even if you are listening & following my music since the very start... THANK YOU! 

This album is my 4th solo album. And with every new solo album I feel that I have pushed my Emotionpsy to the next level. Well it sure happened again with this one, for my 15 years of this project... I feel I have reached another level of emotions , atmospheres and experimental psytrance music.

 I would like to leave you all with these words yet again : 

'You should enjoy the little detours to the fullest. Because that's where you'll find the things more important than what you want.'

 OPEN YOUR MIND, CLOSE YOUR EYES, PRESS PLAY & FLY AWAY ... Yours truly Paul Hoeylaerts.
